22. h3
{ White hopes to catch a breath after h3. But Black keeps going and doesn't allow this. How can we put pressure on the h3-pawn? }
22... Qh4 { Now the typical piece sacrifice is a real danger. } 23. Rc2
{ The rook has to defend the second rank. Black's next move is the typical sacrifice in these types of positions. }
23... Bxh3 24. gxh3 Qxh3
{ If White places the bishop to d3, then it will be more passive than on c4. }
25. Bc4
{ Opening up the second rank for the rook. Our desire is to push our dangerous g-pawn, how can we make that happen? }
25... Nh4 26. Qe2
{ Now White is doing everything in order to stop the push of the g-pawn. Will White succeed? }
26... g2
{ Of course not, we will push the pawn no matter what. Now Black is winning the queen, but White has got compensation for it.   After  27.Nxg2  Rxg2+  28.Qxg2  Nxg2  29.Rxg2  Rg8  30.Rxg8+  Kxg8∞  ,  material is about equal, but the white king remains exposed. }
