{ White has already a big advantage on the queenside. The breakthrough was successful, and White has powerful knights and a strong remote passed pawn on a4.  Without a breakthrough on the other flank, Black will go down slowly but surely. However, White controls the vital g4-square with a lot of pieces... But after several examples, you can tell that this won't stop us. }
24... g4
{ Without this push, Black has no chance for a real attack on the kingside. }
25. fxg4 hxg4 26. hxg4
{ Black cannot take easily the g4-pawn and wants to use the open h-file. We would like to prepare ...Qh6, how can we do that? }
26... Bg5 { ∆ ...Rh7 and ...Qh6, with mating threats on the h-file. } 27. Ra3
{ The white rook wants to defend the third rank. If we put the queen on h6, it would run into Rh3. So what can we do instead? }
27... Rh7 28. Rh3 { White has to neutralize the pressure on the open h-file. }
28... Rxh3 29. gxh3
{ After the exchange of the rooks, White has got a new weakness in his position. How can we immediately attack it? }
29... Qh6 { Yes, with the queen. And the attack continues... } *

