29. Kf1
{ The queen is ideally posted on h6, now the time has come to open up this file! }
29... Nxf3 30. gxf3
{ The logical follow-up  30...Qh1  is kind of a mistake because the king can escape after  31.Ke2  . So instead of that, Black has to blow up White's pawn chain on the kingside. }
30... Nxg4 31. fxg4
{ As I have mentioned before, the white king's only wish is to run away from the kingside, but now it is our turn and we won't let it happen. }
31... f3 { ∆ ...Qh3+ and Black is winning. } *

