33. Nxa8
{ If White eliminates the rook, Black gets a free hand on the kingside with a winning attack. Which piece can help the queen give mate? }
33... Nxg4
{ We do not just take a pawn @@StartBracket@@which by the way is not a big deal in the King's Indian as you already know@@EndBracket@@ but create an easy mate in one threat. }
34. Bg3
{ The bishop temporarily defends against ...Qh2 mate, but leaves the e3-square unprotected. Would you go for the material advantage after ...Ne3, or give a bishop check on e3? }
34... Be3+
{ It wasn't a difficult decision to make, obviously, we give a check and continue the attack! }
35. Rf2 { And now finally comes the great harvest of the white pieces... }
35... Bxf2+ 36. Bxf2
{ Now the bishop is no longer on the g3-square, which is more information than you need to find the next move. }
36... Qh2+ 37. Kf1
{ Bring another piece, which was a 'sleeping beauty' until this moment! } 37...
Ba6+ 38. Ke1 Qxg2
{ Winning the piece, and the dangerous attack against the white king is not vanishing either. }
