23. hxg4
{ White allows Black to change the course of the game and introduce the other attacking plan. We cannot say that the h6-bishop is really bad, but we can definitely say that the position of this bishop can be improved. Where would you maneuver it? }
23... Bg5
{ The bishop is penetrating the dark squares via h4. What a big difference! }
24. Nb5 Bh4 { Remember the bishop's route: h6-g5-h4 and probably g3 later. }
25. Be1 { White wants to fight for the e1-h4 diagonal, but in vain. } 25... Bg3
{ The intruder on g3 creates a lot of mating threats. Black can go for the weak g4-pawn or try to double on the h-file. }
