[SetUp "1"]

23. Ng2
{ White can exchange the f4-knight but Black has another one, eagerly waiting for a vacancy on that square. }
23... Nxg2 24. Kxg2 Nf4+
{ As if nothing has happened, there is again a wonderful knight on f4. } 25.
Kg3
{ Now Black has to bring new pieces for the kingside attack. Which one can be maneuvered to the h-file? }
25... Rf6 { The rook is coming via the 6th rank. } 26. Rh1
{ White defends against the astonishing mating threat on the h-file but leaves the f-file unattended. Let's just open it! }
26... Nxe2+ 27. Qxe2
{ The queen is an overloaded piece, it has to defend the f3-pawn and the b5-knight. How can we force the queen to leave the f3-pawn unprotected? }
27... Bxb5 28. Qxb5
{ The rook is attacking the f3-pawn, who else can attack it? } 28... Qf4+ 29.
Kg2 Qxf3+
{ Black will follow with ...Qxf2+. This motif is working because the rook had to leave the f1-square. }
*

