24. Kh1
{ There are two knights on the h-file, but we still would like to attack there because the game will be decided on the open h-file. }
24... Qh6
{ 24...N5f4  is no longer the way to go since now White has a strong defensive resource:  25.Bg3  , and after  25...Qh6  26.Bh2  , White not only survives but is already for choice according to the engines. }
25. Bh4
{ After  25.gxh5  , Black recaptures and the dangerous threat  is ...Nxf2. Because of that, Black is winning. White desperately wants to close the h-file but in vain. We have to open up the h-file no matter what! }
25... N5f4 26. Ng2 { Protecting the h4-bishop but only for a second. } 26...
Nxg2 27. Kxg2 Qxh4 28. Qe1
{ White cannot really believe that the attacking queen can be exchanged. We wouldn't trade it for a whole world! Continue the attack, and give a check! }
28... Nf4+ 29. Kg1
{ Look at the knight on f4, it is marvelous! Use the help of the f4-knight and prepare the mate! }
29... Qh3 { Black's attack crashes through. } *

