22. c6 { The d7-bishop is under attack, do we bother with it? } 22... Ngf4
{ Of course, we don't waste time dealing with the d7-bishop. We are after the main target: the white king. }
23. cxd7 { Give a check to the white king! } 23... Nh3+ 24. Kh2
{ What should we do with our h3-knight? } 24... Nxf2
{ By exchanging the important f2-bishop, Black gets total control over the dark squares. }
25. Rxf2 { Let's continue what we have started with our queen! } 25... Qh4+ 26.
Kg1 { Who can help the queen now? } 26... Ng3
{ The knight! Now the threat is mate in one on h1. } *

