27. Rf1
{ Vacating the f2-square for the king. We need another piece to cooperate with the queen and the knight, which one can it be? }
27... Bh6
{ The bishop! The direct threat is ...Be3+, but if White parries it, the bishop can find another wonderful square on the c1-h6 diagonal. }
28. Qd3
{ As I have mentioned before, if White doesn't allow the check the bishop can find its place on f4 as well. }
28... Bf4 { Preparing for the final check on h2. } 29. Nc2
{ Let's open up the h2-b8 diagonal! } 29... Nxe2+ 30. Qxe2
{ We have got two possible and tempting checks on h2. Which piece should give this check? The bishop or the queen, not allowing the escape of the king? }
30... Bh2+
{ Here we go, the bishop gives the check, so the king has no escape via f2. }
31. Kh1 { Let's give mate in 2! } 31... Bg3+ 32. Kg1 Qh2# *

