22. Be1
{ White wants to neutralize the pressure on the c1-h6 diagonal in case of ...Bh6 with Bd2, but we don't care about this. }
22... Bh6 23. Bd2
{ Pitkonen-Niemela, corr 1991. White can exchange the bishop, but it is not a real problem for us. }
23... Bxd2
{ After the exchange of the dark-squared bishop, Black has still got pressure on the dark squares. }
24. Rxd2 { Which is the best square for the queen? } 24... Qg5
{ The queen has reached its ideal position for the attack. The rook on d2 is hanging, but the main target is the g2-pawn. }
25. Qc2
{ Protecting the weak rook. Black's aim is to put as much pressure as possible on the g2-pawn. }
25... Bh3 { The second piece has arrived! } 26. Ne1
{ Let's bring the third one! } 26... Nh4 { Here we go! } 27. Bf1
{ The g2-pawn is now overprotected, but the f3-pawn falls. } 27... Rxf3
{ White collapses. } *

