19. Bxa7
{ White takes the other pawn on the queenside and hopes that the opponent cannot get close quickly to the king. Black's major plan is to get rid of the obstacle on the h4-d8 diagonal and bring the queen rapidly to h4. }
19... Nh7
{ Opening up the diagonal for the queen, and the knight may join the battle from g5. }
20. Qc2
{ The white queen is a good attacker on the c-file and a good defender on the 2nd rank. }
20... Qh4 21. h3
{ This is the last barricade, but Black can eliminate it easily. } 21... Bxh3
22. gxh3 Qxh3 23. Bd3
{ Opening up the 2nd rank for the queen. Now the plan is to bring both knights. }
23... Nh4 { The wonderful black knights will show their strength soon. } 24.
Rd1 Ng5 { With an irresistible attack for Black. } *

