19. Be1
{ This is a passive retreat, giving Black a free hand on the kingside. It is impossible to create an impregnable blockade with h2-h3. }
19... h4 { ∆ ...h4-h3, opening up all the files on the kingside. } 20. h3
{ This blockade is easy to blow up. Black has to sacrifice a piece on h3, but we have to put pressure on that pawn with another piece, not just with the bishop. }
20... Nh7
{ There is no defense against the knight maneuver to g5, and then comes the sacrifice on h3. }
21. Kh1
{ ∆ Rg1, Bf1, but White has no space on the kingside for a successful defense. }
21... Ng5 22. Rg1 { Now the question is: which piece should be sacrificed? }
22... Nxh3
{ We would like to keep the bishop. The sacrifice comes just in time; Black gets two pawns and a dangerous attack for the knight. }
23. gxh3 Bxh3 { The black pawns are really impressive, soon ...h4-h3 comes. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
