23. Bb6
{ White wants to avoid the opening of the files and diagonals but cannot hermetically close the position. }
23... gxh2+
{ Now the g3-square becomes weak and if a knight gets there and the queen on h4, Black can create real threats against the white king. }
24. Kxh2 Nh5 { Opening the way for the queen to h4. } 25. Kg1 Ng3 { ∆ ...Qh4 }
26. Bxa6 Qh4
{ This is the ideal setup for the attacking pieces, but in many cases only enough for a draw by repetition of moves:  27.Qd2  Qh1+  28.Kf2  Qh4  29.Kg1=  . }
*

