27. Nd3
{ Here Black can continue the attack since we are not forced to take the draw by perpetual. So which piece can join the battle? }
27... Bf6
{ The bishop can be very annoying if it gets to h4 with a king on f2. } 28. Rc1
{ White allows Black to penetrate to h1. } 28... Qh1+ 29. Kf2
{ How can the bishop join the attack without losing any tempi? } 29... Nxe4+
30. fxe4 Bh4+ { Here we see the main idea of ...Bf6. } 31. Ke2
{ 31.Kf3  is mate in three, starting with  31...Bg4  . } 31... Qxg2+ 32. Nf2
Bg4+ { Winning the queen and the game. } *

