25. Bd3
{ The bishop is defended here, and the 2nd rank is opened, but there is a very big difference if we compare this move with the main line  25.Rc2  . Which square was abandoned by this reckless bishop move? It is not easy to answer now, but you definitely can answer this after a couple of moves... }
25... Qg5 26. g3 Nh3+ 27. Kg2
{ Now comes the big blow! Which square was abandoned by the 25.Bd3 move? }
27... Rxf3 28. Kxf3 { Give a check with the queen! } 28... Qg4+ 29. Kg2
{ Use the pin on the g-file and give another check! } 29... Nf4+ 30. Kg1
{ Now comes the last sacrifice. The g2-square is very weak, let's attack it and mate will come soon! }
30... Qf3 31. gxf4 { And the last attacker comes. } 31... Bh3
{ White cannot prevent the mate. } *

