[SetUp "1"]

{ White has no adequate threats on the queenside. It is Black who comes first on the other flank. }
19... g3 20. hxg3 Nh5 21. gxf4
{ If  21.g4?  , White cannot keep the position closed because after  21...Ng3+  , Black's  plan is ...Ng6 and ...Qh4, with mating threats. Now Black is at a crossroads, how to take back on f4? }
21... exf4
{ In many cases we take back on f4 with our knight, but here it is important to keep the weakness on g3 and open up the long diagonal for the bishop. }
22. Bh4
{ Fighting against both ...Rf6 and ...Ng6. We need to neutralize the pressure on the h4-d8 diagonal. }
22... Bf6 23. Be1 { Let's bring the next important piece! } 23... Ng6 24. Kg1
Ng3 { Placing the knight into White's stomach! } *

