20. Bg1
{ White wants to avoid the opening of the position on the kingside, but this passive retreat doesn't help. Place one of your knights on the best square! }
20... Nh5
{ The target is now the h2-pawn with the maximum pressure via ...Rf6-h6, ...Ng6, and ...Qh4. }
21. h3
{ It seems quite natural, but as we already know, it creates a new target and the punishment cannot wait. Instead of that,  21.Nc6  would have been a better choice. }
21... Bxh3
{ Destroying White's last barricade, winning the important g2 and h3-pawns for the piece. }
22. gxh3 { The h3-pawn is extremely weak, how can we immediately attack it? }
22... Qd7 23. Kg2
{ The king is not a really good defender because it can easily be attacked. Which piece can force the white king to leave the important g2-square? }
23... Ng6 { ∆ ...Nh4+ and the h3-pawn and White's whole defense falls. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
