[SetUp "1"]

25. Rb1 { Our queen is not so active on a8, how can we improve it? } 25... Qa7
{ The queen is a lethal force on the g1-a7 diagonal, pinning the f2-rook. } 26.
Bxb5 Bxb5 27. Rxb5
{ The rook on f2 is pinned. Which piece can put pressure on it beside the queen? }
27... Bf6 { Of course, the bishop via h4! } 28. Kh1
{ Leaving the pin on the g1-a7 diagonal, but running into a nice tactical blow. How can we open up the h-file? }
28... Ng3+ 29. hxg3 fxg3 30. Rf1
{ The queen was completely successful on a7, but that diagonal is empty, there is no pin anymore, so there is no point in keeping the queen there. Now we need the queen on the kingside; how can we bring it there? }
30... Qa8
{ The queen is running back to the kingside with the mating threat of ...Qh6. }
