22. Bb6
{ White has no time to run away with the bishop because Black's attack will be too strong. }
22... Qh4 23. h3
{ Now you already know how to blow up White's pawn structure! } 23... Bxh3
{ Destroying White's defensive wall of pawns. } 24. gxh3 Qxh3
{ The threat to give mate on h2 is too strong so White has to give some material back. }
25. Rf2 { Otherwise, the mate is inevitable. } 25... gxf2+ 26. Kxf2 Qg3+ 27.
Kf1 Nh4
{ With an irresistible attack on the kingside. Look at the gorgeous knights! The rook will join the party soon from g7. }
