26. Bf2 { The safety of the king is more important than material gains. } 26...
bxc1=Q 27. Rxc1 { Let's open up the diagonal of the c8-bishop! } 27... Nf6
{ ∆ ...Bh3, with a strong attack against the weakness on g2, so White's answer is more or less forced.  28.Qxc8  is a nice positional queen sacrifice. White gets a rook and a piece for it.  28...Rxc8  29.Rxc8+  Ng8∞  ,  with immense complications. Black still has some pressure on the kingside, but the real attack is already far away. }
