20... Ng6 21. Bg5
{ Unlike in case of 20.Qd2, this move is now possible. White wants to provoke ...h6, avoiding the rook shift to h6 from f6. That is why Black doesn't want to play ...h6; so what else can we do if we keep ...Nh5 as the next move in our mind? }
21... Qc8
{ Leaving the pin and threatening ...Nh5 followed by ...h6, capturing the bishop. }
22. Bxf6 Rxf6 { ∆ ...Nh4 and ...Rh6. } 23. Re1
