26. Qa1
{ ∆ a4-a5, opening up the a-file and continuing the attack on the queenside. Now comes a big surprise! In almost all of our diagram positions, we show a beautiful sacrifice or an aggressive attacking move.  This time the solution is completely different! White's a4-a5 threat is quite strong, let's do something against it! }
26... Ra5
{ Instead of a brilliant firework on the kingside, Black quietly blockades the queenside, depriving White of any counterplay on that flank. }
27. Ne1
{ White is defending the kingside by all means. However, White's fate is sealed. We have already seen the next combination. }
27... Nf5
