22... Ng4
{ This is the big surprise, the knight jumps on the minefield without being hurt. }
23. Qe2
{ White has to allow the impertinent knight to jump on e3.   23.fxg4  is a huge mistake, as after  23...hxg4  , Black  can plan ...f3 and White's whole position collapses! }
23... Ne3 24. Rea1
{ White is still dreaming of opening files on the queenside with a4-a5. White's weakest pawn is the h3 one, so let's put pressure on it! }
24... Qc8
{ Controlling the vital h3-c8 diagonal. A sacrifice on g2 and h3 is always hanging in the air. }
