[SetUp "1"]

{ Black's first move is a trivial piece sacrifice, the immense complications are coming after that. }
26... Nxh3 27. gxh3 Qxh3+ 28. Kg1
{ The well-known defensive move is Qg2. Black cannot allow this. } 28... Nh4
{ Black has a simple plan of ...Bf8 and ...Rg7 followed by ...g2. White has to do something against it. }
29. Be8 { White is fighting against the black rook on the g-file. } 29... Rf6
{ The black rook has no direct access to g6, but ...Kf8 can drive away the bishop from the h5-e8 diagonal. }
30. Qc2
{ Black has to deflect the knight from the defense of the f3-pawn.   30.Bxh5  runs into the beautiful  30...Nf5  31.Bg4  Qh8!  32.Bxf5  Rh6  33.Be6+  Kf8  34.Qg2  Rh2  , with a winning position for Black. }
30... g2 31. Nxg2 Nxf3+ 32. Rxf3 Qxf3
{ White is a bit better from a material point of view, but Black still has some attacking prospects on the kingside. The chances are equal in a very complicated position. }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
