[SetUp "1"]

23. Bb5
{ White takes away the d7-square from the queen and threatens with the penetrating move 24.Rc7. }
23... Nd7
{ Let's just open up the cardinal h4-d8 diagonal for the queen and attack the strong b6-bishop at the same time. }
24. Rc7
{ Black has a simple plan, ...Qh4-h2 mate, but the h3-bishop is now a painful obstackle. How can we get rid of it? }
24... Bf5
{ An immediate  24...Qh4?  allows White to take  on h3 and defend from the 2nd rank:  25.gxh3  Qxh3  26.Qc2  . With the text move, Black opens up the h-file for the queen,  when it gets to h4. Any other bishop moves would give White the advantage! }
25. exf5 Qh4 { With a winning attack for Black. } *

