28. a6 Rcxc7 29. Qxc7 Rxc7 30. Rxc7 bxa6 31. Bxa6
{ White's weak point is the h3-pawn, let's attack it! } 31... Qh4 32. Bc8
{ 32.Kg2  also defends  the h3-pawn, but runs later into a strong ...Nh4 move. Now comes an unexpected retreat! }
32... Qd8
{ Black is vacating the h4-square for the knight, and the queen gets to the important g1-a7 diagonal. }
33. Rc2 Qb6+ 34. Kh1 Nh4
