19. h4
{ White doesn't want to allow the opening of the kingside. We want to take on h4, but which piece is suitable for that? }
19... Ng6
{ The knight for sure! We're planning ...Nxh4, keeping the h-file open for the queen and the rook. }
20. g4
{ Creating some space around the white king.  20.Nxd6  instead allows Black to unfold the attack unhindered:  20...Nxh4  21.Bxh4  Qxh4  and now the threat of  22.--  Qh2  23.Kf2  Qg3  24.Kg1  Rh2  followed by ...Qh4 is hard to parry. }
20... fxg3 21. Bxg3 { Our c5-knight is hanging, what should we do with it? }
21... Nxd3 22. Bxd3
{ 22.f4  would be a nice zwischenzug but Black has also a witty intermediate move on that:  22...Nxb2! }
22... Nf4 { With a very strong attack against the white king. } *

