24. Kg2 { Do we want to escape with the rook or keep it there and protect it? }
24... Qd7
{ The rook is fantastic on h3, so the queen had to protect it and it creates a mating threat at the same time. }
25. Rg1 { Clearing the f1-square for the retreat of the king. } 25... f3+ 26.
Kf1
{ If White takes the pawn with  26.Nxf3  , after  26...Qg4  Black wins the knight. Where should we put the rook creating additional motifs?  Black wants to give a big check with the queen on h3, but the h3-rook is now an obstacle. }
26... Rh4
{ This is the best square for the rook because in some variations ...Rxe4 will come with lethal threats. }
27. Bxh4 Qh3+ 28. Kf2
