30... Nxf2 31. Kxf2
{ White's plan is to play Rh1 followed by Ke1 and Kd2 and the king is safe in the middle of the board. Black has to keep the white king on the kingside.   31...h1=Q  looks logical but after  32.Rxh1  Qxh1  33.Bf1  , the king survives and White has got an extra piece.  So let's prepare for the dangerous ...Qg3+ move somehow! }
