{ The a8-rook is hanging, and the black pawn structure is about to collapse on the queenside, so it is high time to show something concrete on the other flank. }
22... Nxg2
{ Black ignores the hanging rook and on top of that, Black sacrifices a knight! By eliminating the defensive g2-pawn, the g- and h-files become opened, when Black has to bring the strongest piece, the queen, into action. }
23. bxc7 { The queen and the rook are hanging; which piece will make a move? }
23... Ng4+
{ Certainly, it is the knight. We open up the h4-d8 diagonal for the queen. }
24. fxg4 { Finally, the queen can join the attack. } 24... Qh4+ 25. Kxg2
{ Black has sacrificed a lot of material, but a single queen can rarely give mate. }
25... Qg3+ 26. Kh1 { We need to bring new pieces into the fight! } 26... Rf6
{ ∆ ...Rh6# } *

