{ There are a lot of threats, for example ...Qg3.   Instead,  29...Qg3  immediately gives White hope for survival. After  30.Nd3  Nxe4  @@StartBracket@@now  30...Rh7  can be met by  31.Qf2  @@EndBracket@@ @@StartFEN@@r1N2bk1/1p4r1/p2p4/3Pp3/P3n1p1/3NBpq1/1PQ3P1/2RBR1K1 w - - 0 31@@EndFEN@@  31.Bf4  exf4  32.Rxe4  Rh7  33.Nxf4  Rxc8  34.Qxc8  f2+  35.Kf1  Rh1+  36.Ke2  Re1+   36...f1=Q  doesn't lead anywhere, as after  37.Kd2  , Black has to give up a  queen on f4 in order to avoid mate, or allow perpetual in some typical computer-like variations.  37.Kd2  , Black can even lose if not careful and greedily promotes queen. White's position is still worse according to the engine, but why enter such muddy waters in the first place? }
