{ Since the g-file is now opened, Black can already take the rook and give a check on g3 or g5. }
26. Nxf2 { 26.Bxf2  simply loses material after  26...Qg5  and ...Rxc7. } 26...
Qg3+ 27. Kh1
{ Black has to continue the attack with forced moves, avoiding the defensive move Qg1. }
27... f3 { Deflecting the bishop to a vulnerable square. } 28. Bxf3
{ Since the bishop is on f3 where it can easily be attacked, let's bring a piece and attack it immediately! }
28... Nh4 29. Ra3
