29. Bxh2 gxh2
{ Suddenly it becomes clear that Black will promote a new queen very quickly! }
30. Qb6
{ Preparing to answer on  30...h1=Q  with  31.Qg1  . Is there any alternative for Black? }
30... e3
{ Black closes the g1-a7 diagonal because there is no defense against the promotion of the queen.   White is in such a tough spot that even promoting immediately works:  30...h1=Q+  31.Qg1  Qxg1+  32.Kxg1  exf3  33.gxf3  Bd4+!  34.Rxd4  Nhxf3+  35.Nxf3  Nxf3+  36.Kf1  Nxd4  , with a winning endgame for Black. However, the text is more precise. }
31. Ke2 h1=Q
{ The position is materially equal, but the white king cannot be saved from the attack. }
