{ White did not achieve much on the queenside yet. Conquering the a-file is a double-edged operation because the queen has left the important d1-h5 diagonal. Why is it an important factor? How can we get an advantage on it? }
21... Nxg4
{ Yes, we need to destroy White's defensive wall! White may think that the g4-pawn was well-defended, as Black can only get one pawn for the knight. But our opponent couldn't be further from the truth! }
22. fxg4
{ The knight has to be taken. There is no time to insert  22.cxd6  or  22.cxb6  because Black has the natural zwischenzug  22...Nxf2  . Now we can see the main idea: the knight sacrifice  deflected the f3-pawn and made the f4-pawn a game-changer. }
