{ Let's bring new pieces into the attack! } 25... Nf4 26. Bxf4
{ The strong bishop has to be eliminated, but first, let's give a check to the white king!  26...exf4  immediately is also winning. }
26... Qg2+ 27. Ke1
{ It goes without saying which pawn will take the f4-bishop. } 27... exf4
{ Opening up the long diagonal and creating three dangerous pawns on the kingside.  28.Bxf3  is strongly met by  28...Qc2  and both knights are hanging. Otherwise, Black will push the g-pawn followed  by ...Bf6, and the white king in the middle cannot survive the attack. }
