{ White has already annihilated Black's queenside and the a8-rook is hanging. What shall we do? }
26... h3
{ Black ignores the hanging a8-rook, threatening mate in one on the other flank. }
27. g4
{ White wants to keep the h3-pawn alive because it may protect the king. Black cannot allow the closing of the g-file. }
27... fxg3+ 28. Bxg3
{ It is very important to look for unprotected pieces, and a double attack may win material. }
28... Qe3 29. Qxa8
{ 29.Re1  protects the bishop but loses the knight after  29...Rxa7  . } 29...
Qxe2+
{ After  30.Nf2  , the knight and bishop try to defend the king, but all the other pieces are far away from the kingside. Let's bring the rook to the attack!  30...Rxf3  31.Rf1  , let's eliminate the strong defensive piece!  31...Rxg3!  0–1 Kjartansson-Kavutskiy, Reykjavik 2017.  32.Kxg3  and now it is a forced mate in 4 moves:  32...Qe3+  33.Kh2  Qf4+  34.Kh1  Qf3+  35.Kg1  Qg2#  . }
