[SetUp "1"]

{ White has already taken on a8 so is a rook up. How should we fight back? }
21... h3
{ Black has to open up the files on the kingside for the queen and rook, which form a dangerous battery. }
22. g4
{ The h-file remains closed, otherwise, a quick mate is coming.  22.g3  fxg3  transposes to the main line. }
22... fxg3 23. Bxg3
{ The g-file is open; White is threatening Kh2, leaving Black without any chances. }
23... h2+ 24. Kh1
{ The king looks fairly safe on h1, but this can be deceptive. The target is the undefended g3-bishop. }
24... Qh3 25. Bxe5
{ The g3-bishop cannot be saved.  25.Qe1?  loses to  25...Nh5-+  . Now Black has to find a beautiful attacking move, otherwise, we can get into trouble! }
25... Nh5
{ 25...dxe5?  falls into the trap:  26.Nf2  Qh4  27.d6  , which changes the course of the game. }
26. Nf2 { The e5-bishop has to be sacrificed, ...Ng3+ is the big threat. }
26... Qh4 27. Ng4 dxe5 28. Nxh6+ Bxh6
{ White is two exchanges up, but Black's attack remains very dangerous. } *

