[SetUp "1"]

24. Kf2
{ White wants to leave the kingside running towards the middle of the board. Don't allow this! }
24... Rg6 { We simply cannot allow Ke3. } 25. Rh1
{ The target is the g3-bishop. Let's attack it! } 25... Qh3 26. Bxh2
{ Bring the next piece into the battle! } 26... Bh6
{ 26...Qg2  27.Ke3  lets the white king slip away. } 27. Ke1
{ ∆ Nf2, bringing back the knight to the defense. Attack one of White's pieces immediately! }
27... Qg2 28. Nf2
{ The white pieces are completely tied, which is the next target? } 28... Be3
{ The knight, which is defending the h1-rook! } 29. Rf1
{ White protects the knight, the best defender, and leaves the bishop to fall. }
29... Qxh2 30. Rc3
{ The bishop on e3 is ideally posted, so we need to keep it there. } 30... Qf4
31. Rxe3
{ The bishop was better than the rook, but now White has no more material advantage. }
31... Qxe3 { And the black pieces totally dominate the board. } *

