25. Rf2 { A very tricky defense. How do we continue our attack? } 25... Nh5
{ The target remains, but instead of taking it, we attack it with the knight. }
26. Bxh2
{ So the bishop escaped, but both the g- and h-files are now open. On the immediate  36...Ng3?  the white king escapes after  37.Kg1  , so let's prepare that check! }
26... Rg6
{ Now ...Ng3+ is a lethal check, White's only chance is to sacrifice the queen. }
27. Qg1 Rxg1+ 28. Rxg1 Qh4
{ The position is materially about equal, White has two rooks for the queen. However, Black's attack remains very strong; ...Ng6-f4 loos very promising. }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
