25. gxh3 { This is a big mistake because of the typical... } 25... g3
{ Now the g- and the h-files can easily be opened, and the g3-pawn creates a lot of mating motifs. }
26. Rg1
{ Black has to bring the queen for the attack to h5, therefore a temporary retreat with the g6-knight is required. }
26... Ne7 { Clearing the g-file and the h5-e8 diagonal. } *

