29. Qc3
{ White wants to defend the e1-h4 diagonal. Find the best continuation for Black. }
29... Qh4 { ∆  30.--  g2  31.Kh2  Qg3  . } 30. Qe1
{ ...g2+ is not a threat anymore, but ...Qh4 was a double attack because the f4-pawn was under scrutiny as well. }
30... exf4 { The strong kingside pawns decide the battle. } *

