[SetUp "1"]

{ White has not done much on the queenside, there are no threats yet. Black already advanced the pawns on the other flank, they all reached the 4th rank. Let's blow up White's kingside! }
18... h3 19. fxg4
{ 19.gxh3?  is strongly met by the typical pawn sacrifice of  19...g3!-+  . }
19... hxg2+ 20. Kxg2 Bxg4 { 20...Nxg4  was also good. } 21. Bxg4 Nxg4 22. Kh1
{ This is the safest place for the king. Now comes a very important prophylactic move; the devotees of the King's Indian know it well. }
22... Rf7
{ Black defends the 7th rank and prepares ...Bf8 or even ...Raf8 depending on the circumstances. }
23. Rf3
{ The rook is not the best blockade. On  23.Ne1  Nh4  comes with a strong attack. Now it is high time to attack with our queen. }
23... Qg5 24. Qc2 { Defending the 2nd rank. } 24... Raf8
{ Even if the f3-square is well-blockaded, our threat is ...Ne3, and when the knight is taken, the f-file will be open for the rooks. }
*

