[SetUp "1"]

19. g3
{ This push looks like a logical defense because the g3-pawn takes away the squares from the active g6-knight. On the other hand, that pawn is the last barricade; if it falls, White's position collapses. }
19... fxg3 20. hxg3
{ So let's attack the cornerstone of White's defense by all means! } 20... Nh5
21. Bh2
{ It may seem that White can protect the g3-pawn, but now comes the typical sacrifice! }
21... Ngf4 { If White accepts the sacrifice, the g4-pawn can freely advance. }
22. gxf4 g3 { White has to give material back. } 23. Bxg3 Nxg3+ 24. Kh2 Nxf1+
25. Rxf1 exf4 { Now it is Black who is a clear exchange up. } *

