[SetUp "1"]

{ It seems that White comes first on the queenside. The c7-pawn is hanging and cannot be protected by @@StartFEN@@3q1rk1/2pb2b1/3p1nn1/BN1Pp2p/2P1Ppp1/3N1P2/4B1PP/3Q1R1K b - - 0 23@@EndFEN@@  23...Ne8  because of  24.fxg4  .  Black's typical attacking plan is ...g3 and ...Qh4. How can we make the procedure quicker? }
23... Nxd5
{ Opening up the h4-d8 diagonal and temporary protecting the c7-pawn. } 24.
cxd5 g3 { ∆ ...Qh4xh2 mate. } 25. h3
{ Now instead of h2, the h3-pawn becomes the primary target. Let's bring the most valuable piece to the attack. }
25... Qh4 26. Kg1
{ Running out of the h-file. We need to demolish White's defensive pawn structure. }
26... Bxh3 27. gxh3 Qxh3 28. Rf2
{ Otherwise, ...Qh2 mate is coming. Do we hurry with ...gxf2+? } 28... Nh4
{ 28...gxf2  would also win, but we can wait a bit... } 29. Qf1
{ Now we are forced to take the rook. } 29... gxf2+ 30. Nxf2 Qg3+ 31. Kh1
{ It is time for the second wave of the attack... } 31... Ra8
{ The rook belongs to the open file, it will penetrate on the a-file. } *

