[SetUp "1"]

23. exd5 { Once again, White allows the typical winning attack. } 23... Qh4 24.
h3 { Let's destroy White's defensive wall of pawns! } 24... Bxh3 25. gxh3 Qxh3
26. Bd1
{ Opening the 2nd rank for the queen. Qg2 can be a good defensive move, we do not let it happen. }
26... Nh4 27. Ra2
{ Overprotecting the 2nd rank. Now comes the final countdown! Make the f3-pawn go away! }
27... e4 { With a double threat of taking on d3 and f3. } 28. fxe4
{ Now the blockading f3-pawn is kicked out! } 28... f3
{ The two connected passed pawns on the 3rd rank finish the game in style.   After the hasty  28...g2  , the tables turn in White's favor:  29.Qxg2  Nxg2  30.Rf3  Qd7  31.c6  Qe7  32.Rxg2  and Black is suddenly on the wrong side of things. }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
