26. gxh5
{ White wins a pawn and attacks the g6-knight, but opens up the g-file. Do we move away the attacked knight? }
26... Qg5 { Certainly not, we counterattack the weakness on g2. } 27. Bf1
{ White wants to overprotect the weak g2-pawn. } 27... Qxh5
{ Eliminating the h5-pawn, and a file is already open on the kingside. } 28.
Bxc7
{ White also continues the assault on the queenside. Now the d6-pawn is hanging, what can we do about it? }
28... Bf6
{ We completely ignore it, we have bigger threats like ...Bh4-g3 and ...Rh7, with a winning attack. }
