28. Kh1 { The d3-knight is still not important. What do we do? } 28... Bxh3
{ Certainly, we don't take it, but sacrifice our bishop! } 29. gxh3
{ The immediate  29...Qh4?  loses to the simple  30.Bf1  , defending everything. How do we continue our attack? }
29... g2+ { We open the g-file and vacate the g3-square for the queen. } 30.
Kxg2 Qh4 { There is no defense against ...Qg3+. } 31. Rh1
{ Protecting the h3-pawn and clearing the way for the king to f1. } 31... Qg3+
32. Kf1 { Now comes the final blow, a new piece joins the attack. } 32... Nh4
{ White collapses on the weaknesses of f3 and g2. } *

