{ White was preparing against this push with a desperate queen sacrifice. After  28.Qxg2  Nxg2  29.Rxg2  Ng3  , White has only a rook and a knight for the queen, but the biggest problem is the delicate position of the king.  30.Re1  Qc8–+  and the queen had a wonderful position but it was not easy to continue the attack on the kingside. So Black changes the course of the game and penetrates from the queenside. Tanis-Van Tienhoven, corr 2011. }
