27. Qxf3 { The queen is by far not the best blockading piece. } 27... Bg4 28.
Qd3 { The bishop on h4 is vulnerable, let's attack it! } 28... Ng6 29. Bg5
{ White wants to keep the bishop on the h4-d8 diagonal, but it will not last long. }
29... Qf7
{ The natural  29...Rag8  allows unnecessary complications after  30.Nc5!  Black is still better following  30...Nf8  @@StartBracket@@the knight is taboo:  30...dxc5  runs into  31.d6  @@EndBracket@@ @@StartFEN@@5nrk/1p2q1r1/p2p1n2/P1NPp1Bp/1PB1Ppb1/3Q4/6PP/2R2R1K w - - 0 31@@EndFEN@@  31.Bh4  , but part of the advantage has been spilled. }
30. Nb6 { Forcing the last remaining piece to the attack. } 30... Rag8
{ With nasty threats on the semi-opened g-file. } *

[Event "?"]
