24. Kf1 { White allows the h-pawn to run towards the 1st rank. } 24... h2 25.
Ke1
{ All the moves are winning, but let's go for a beautiful sacrifice allowing the breakthrough on the kingside. }
25... Bg4 26. fxg4
{ Now the f3-pawn is deflected from the defense of the e4-pawn. } 26... Nxe4
{ There is a big threat of promoting the h-pawn. } *

