[SetUp "1"]

{ The a8-rook is hanging and Ne6 is also a threat, neutralizing the important c8-bishop. What should Black do about that? }
22... gxh3
{ Black has to open up the g-file, this is the last moment for it. The attack on the kingside outweighs the material losses. }
23. Nxa8
{ The natural move is  23...Rxg2  ,  but it is too early here. Let's save the c8-bishop! }
23... Bd7
{ Black first secures the bishop, as the g2-pawn is a real target and cannot run away.   Surprisingly enough, the immediate  23...Rxg2?  helps White to bring the rook to g1 after  24.Kh1  Bd7  25.Rg1+-  . }
24. Nc7 Rxg2+ 25. Kh1
{ Black has again the same choice of knight moves as before. } 25... Nh7 26.
Rg1 Qg5
{ After  27.Nxh3  ,  White has to sacrifice back some material to avoid immediate loss.   27.Ne6  allows  27...Qg3  with a quick mate.  27...Bxh3  28.Bxf4  exf4  29.Bd3  Rxc2  30.Rxg5+  Nxg5  31.Rxc2  Nxf3-+  ,  with a winning material advantage for Black. }
