24. a6
{ White ignores Black's attack on the kingside, but this is not a wise decision. }
24... Rxg2+ 25. Kh1
{ Now we will open the h4-d8 diagonal for the queen, which wants to get to g5. }
25... Nh7
{ This is the best square for the knight as we'll see it later; from h7 it protects the g5-queen. }
26. Rg1 Qg5 27. Nxh3
{ 27.axb7  allows Black to give mate after  27...Qg3-+  . } 27... Bxh3 28. Bxf4
{ White wants to open up the 2nd rank in order to profit from the pin on the g-file. }
