27. Bg4
{ White gives back the bishop in order to close the g-file. @@StartFEN@@N1b2bkn/pp6/3p4/P2Pp1qB/4Pp2/7p/1PQB1Nr1/2R2R1K w - - 0 27@@EndFEN@@  27.Rg1??  controls the g2-square, but after  27...Qg3  , White gets mated on  the h2-square. }
27... Bxg4 28. Qb3
{ Controlling the 3rd rank is the only chance for a successful defense. It is advisable to ask, which is our worst piece and how can we improve it? }
28... Ng6 29. Nxg4 { This is again the only defense. } 29... Qxg4 30. Qf3
{ The queen has to come back to defend His Majesty. } 30... Rg1+
{ Nice, but it is only enough for perpetual checks. } 31. Kh2
{ The rook was taboo because of the hanging queen. } 31... Rg2+ 32. Kh1
