29. Nxh3
{ White opens up the h-file; at least the h3-pawn defended the white king in a way. Let's profit from the opened h-file! }
29... Qh5
{ It may seem that we just lost our g2-rook, but one has to calculate further! }
30. Kxg2 { We need to create an obstacle on the 3rd rank. } 30... f3+ 31. Kf2
{ 31.Rxf3  simply loses to  31...Nh4-+  . } 31... Qxh3
{ White is still a rook and an exchange up, but the king is hopeless. } 32. Qc4
{ Controlling the e2-square in case of  32...Qg2?  33.Ke1  . Which is the last piece not participating yet in the attack? }
32... Be7 { Yes, it is the bishop; ∆ ...Bh4+. } 33. Ke1
{ The king wants to move to the queenside via Kd1-c2. Black cannot allow the enemy king to escape. }
33... f2+ { Opening up the d1-g4 diagonal for the bishop. } 34. Rxf2 Bh4
{ The pin is the tactician's famous weapon... } *

