[SetUp "1"]

{ The a8-rook is hanging, but if it moves away, Ne6 comes and the h3-pawn is more or less safe. So Black has to come out with a radical solution. }
28... gxh3
{ Black sacrifices the rook in order to launch a big attack on the g-file. }
29. Nxa8
{ The c8-bishop is attacked, so Black has a choice between the immediate  29...Bd7  , or to insert  29...Rxg2  first and after  30.Kh1  , then  30...Bd7  . The decision is far from easy! }
29... Bd7
{ This looks a bit more flexible.  29...Rxg2  30.Kh1  Bd7  31.Nxh3  Bxh3  gives White an extra possibility to defend with  32.Rg1  . }
30. Nxh3
{ White sacrifices back the knight but gets precious time to defend the g2-pawn. }
30... Bxh3 31. Rf2 Qxa8
{ Black has two knights versus the rook, but at least the g2-pawn is well-protected. }
