[SetUp "1"]

30. g4 { White wants to close the g- and h-files. } 30... fxg3
{ The connected passed pawns on the 3rd rank are fearsome. } 31. Nxh3
{ White sacrifices back the knight, but this is only a temporary relief. }
31... Bxh3 32. Bxh6
{ The rook is attacked, and we desperately need it, so there is no second rook sacrifice. }
32... Rg8 33. Bxf8 Qxf8
{ White has an extra rook, but two pieces are hanging at the same time and the connected passed pawns on the h- and g-files cause a lot of headaches for White. }
34. Nc7 { Do we take the f1-rook or join the queen in the battle? } 34... Qh6
{ Of course not! It is neither a good defender nor a good attacker. We bring our queen to the attack threatening ...Qe3+. }
35. Qc3
{ Defending the 3rd rank. Black's main trump is the connected passed pawns. }
35... h4 { With nasty threats like ...Nh5-f4, or ...Bd7 followed by ...h3. } *

