27. gxh3
{ White opens up the g-file, but how can we attack the weakness of h3? Now comes a fantastic sacrifice in order to get more squares on the h3-c8 diagonal. The knight is very passive on the edge of the board, what should we do with it? }
27... Nf5 28. Nc6 Qg5+ 29. Kh2
{ We would like to put the queen to h4, how can we manage to do that? } 29...
Ng3 { ∆ ...Qh4 and ...Qxh3+. } 30. Nxb8
