{ A lot of pieces are hanging, among them the b4-knight and the f3-pawn. When analyzing a tactical position, we always start with checks, then captures, and finally with attacks.  In this case, we obviously focus on the kingside, so the b4-knight is not relevant. How can Black continue the attack against the king? }
21... Nf4
{ Black ignores all the captures and concentrates on the weak g2-pawn. } 22.
Nxf3
